reviews.review: What I wanted to watch. Entertaining, emotional, for us, the  fans! Great!

It wasn't the best Star Wars movie but at least it was the best Star Wars movie from the sequels. You can tell that this movie tries to solve the disaster that the Last Jedi was and that is somewhat satisfying. However, by doing that it feels like they had to put 3 movies into one. They had to set up a new villain, tell Rey's and Poe's backstory and had to connect everything back to the original saga. I feel that they made the best of what they could with the material they had. Disney should have created an outline for the entire trilogy because this trilogy turned out to be a mess...
Does this movie have flaws? YES! Did I still enjoy the hell outta it? SHIT YES! It's all about nostalgia and sending off the old guard! Goodbye Carrie. We will miss you, Space Mom!
Very satisfying end to the saga
Overall decent and entertaining. Although, it seemed rushed in places. Unfortunately, this is what happens when there are no story developments in the previous film.

It is funny and entertaining, but a little confuse and messy, frenetic, lack of more dialogues, characters development and explanations about important events, many plot holes. It is a acceptable ending, but not a brilliant movie, not excellent, it is just good. Empire Strikes Back stills the best.

My kids and I had a lot of fun watching this film. Is it perfect? No; few movies are. But it has a lot of heart, endearing characters and it looks beautiful (it was fantastic in 3D). Given that there was no real plan for this trilogy when they made The Force Awakens, the writers deserve a lot of credit for tying things together so well. All the performances were top notch. They also make wonderful use of the limited footage they had of Carrie Fisher. I'm sure that, like The Last Jedi, this movie will get a lot of criticism. But, I feel sure that the characters of Rey, Finn and Poe will endure; in large part to this film.
The worst movie of the saga.

I loved it. As a kid back in the 80's, didn't read reviews before watching a film and decided not to this time. To go in pure and true to my own feelings. The trilogy makes perfect sense and made me kinda like a TLJ . Thank you to all involved.
